==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Torpedo tube
<hw>Torpedo tube</hw>. <fld>(Nav.)</fld> <def>A tube fixed below or near
the water line through which a torpedo is fired, usually by a small
charge of gunpowder. On torpedo vessels the tubes are on deck and
usually in broadside, on larger vessels usually submerged in broadside
and fitted with a movable shield which is pushed out from the vessel's
side to protect the torpedo until clear, but formerly sometimes in the
bow. In submarine torpedo boats they are in the bow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torpent</ent>⟦br⟧
